I added the word "victorious" before "great powers" and changed "became" to "becoming".  "Victorious" differentiates between the great powers that won the war and those which lost it and temporarily lost their status.  "Becoming" is the correct tense, because "with" precedes it in the sentence, not "while".  Please carefully consider grammar.
